{"key":"processedPost-15358209","value":{"id":15358209,"first":15357830,"last":15358218,"when":1321077020,"utime":"11/12/11 07:50 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>northwest cap said:</b><br />is it possible to take a spore syringe and inject into distilled water. put water in spray bottle and go spray ideal places for patches? if there is a thread already covering this please share the link. the spores would be for P. cyans<br /><br />thanks in advance for help!<br /></blockquote><br /><br />I'm not aware of anyone successfully pulling that off.&nbsp; It would take years at least to get a patch established that way, if at all.<br /><br />Growers have established wood-lover patches by placing several dozen fresh and crushed mushroom caps of the desired species in a bucket of water to make a slurry and then pouring that over a sawdust and woodchip bed.&nbsp; This provides both spores and live mycelium as the inoculant.<br />RR","title":"Re: question about spraying outdoors"}}